    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. that's a good start. could you add a little more warmth to it though? like, maybe something that acknowledges how much effort they put into the final technical interview specifically? i don't want it to feel too robotic or cold since they were actually a really great person.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Ah, you're absolutely right! Adding a touch of warmth is crucial, especially when dealing with a candidate who clearly put in the effort and showed genuine passion. It's a bit like a well-tuned gear system; if one part feels stiff, the whole machine grinds.\n\nHere is the revised draft with a warmer tone, acknowledging their hard work in the interview:\n\n***\n\n**Subject:** Update on Your Application for Senior Developer Role\n\nDear [Candidate Name],\n\nThank you so much for taking the time to interview with us for our Senior Developer position in Austin. We were truly impressed by your system design skills and your strong alignment with our company culture. It was a genuine pleasure getting to know you.\n\nAfter careful consideration, we have decided to move forward with a candidate who has slightly more specific experience with our current cloud infrastructure stack. We know this is a difficult decision, especially given how much effort you put into the final technical interview and how well you matched our core values.\n\nWe sincerely appreciate your interest in our team and wish you the very best in your job search. We hope our paths cross again in the future.\n\nWarmly,\n\n[Your Name]\n[Your Title]\n\n***\n\n**A few",
      "source": "target",
